# Globals live in `.bss`, which is zero at boot (the loader zeroes it, and QEMU's
# ELF loader zeroes the NOBITS span of a bare-metal image). The verifier models a
# global's initial value as 0 to match, so a shared counter can be read before any
# write -- the basis for lock-free work claiming. Here the unwritten global reads
# 0, proven at compile time and confirmed at runtime.
counter: global u32
t0 = &counter
t1 = t0[0:4]          # read the unwritten global
a0 = 0
require t1 == a0      # it is zero
exit(0)
